---
title: Asparagus, Edamame & Chicken Fried Rice with Chicken Thighs, Peas, Sesame Seeds & Scallions
description: The fresh and vibrant flavors of asparagus, edamame, and peas come together in a flash to create an irresistible vegan fried rice. Garlic and ginger add savory aromatic depth, while nutty sesame oil and umami-rich soy sauce combine to make a savory, tangy sauce. Sprinkle sesame seeds over the top to impart delightful crunch with every bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/661568c911089628acd331af-3ee68a78.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6616f01617c952d87280a8d2.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/asparagus-edamame-and-chicken-fried-rice-6616f01617c952d87280a8d2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 740 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 88 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1640 mg
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{3/4%cup} and @water{1 1/4%cups}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to use in a later step.

> Use 2¼ cups water for 4 servings.

Remove chicken from packaging. Rinse @diced chicken thighs{10%oz} under cold water. Pat chicken dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%oz}; cut stalks crosswise into 1-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add asparagus, scallion whites, and @edamame{4%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{4%minutes}.

Add garlic and ginger; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Remove pan from heat.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

To pan with asparagus and edamame mixture, add @peas{4%oz}, rice, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, half the @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, and half the @sesame oil{1%tbsp} (all for 4 servings). Stir to combine.

Return pan to high heat. Cook, stirring occasionally, until rice mixture is warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Stir in chicken along with peas, rice, vinegar, soy sauce, and sesame oil.

Press rice mixture into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on bottom, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Taste and season with remaining soy sauce if desired.

Divide fried rice between shallow #bowls{}. Garnish with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tbsp}. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.